<br>
I've been staring at this thread for a while now, reading and rereading everything and trying to think how I feel about it. One part of me tells me that Kellory's opening line &quot;tried before and failed&quot; is very true, but the other half of me is undecided.<br>
<br>
At the time when Fellowship attempted to move people into other rotations, the average raiding lvl person was 45 - 50ish. Taking on a dragon with anything below about lvl 55+ is... well quite frankly insanity.<br>
<br>
The average lvl on the server has gone up quite a bit, skills expanded etc but I still dont know that there are really enough people that are high enough. Before I have people thinkin I'm a pescimist, hear me out.<br>
<br>
1) just cause someone says they &quot;can&quot; be there does NOT mean they &quot;will&quot; be there<br>
<br>
2) VS must be done with people not already in a rotation. How many 55+ people do you know that havn't moved up to a guild with some rotations? Can you name 5 lvl 60+ people in small &quot;nameless&quot; guilds? What about that many in the same guild?<br>
<br>
3) I firmly believe that sending anyone into the battle below lvl 55ish is insanity and asking to loose.<br>
<br>
4) resists and &quot;gear&quot; lvls are pretty crutial wether we like thinking about it that way or not. Wearin that shiny suit of Crafted / Fine Plate / Ivy Etched etc just will NOT cut it.<br>
<br>
5) how many people can put resistances on their own up to or exceeding 150? The lower you are, the higher your base resist MUST be.<br>
<br>
<br>
Well I'm sure you see the trend going there. I'm not trying to crush anyones thoughts, I am giving you a different perspective. And if you're one of the people in the back of your mind saying &quot;she's talkin crazy, pfft ignore that post&quot; then you are the reason for CoG possibly failing.<br>
<br>
I dont say this stuff cause I dunno, I say it cause I kill him, often. Lemme tell you how we kill him, just for fun <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
VS is called, guild starts porting to DL and running to krapnors. When about 1 group is in, start makin our way to VS. Usually by the time the 6th member of the group arrives in the room, he's dead.<br>
<br>
Don't go overboard on strategy, your biggest concern is DPS. The faster you do dmg, the faster you win. If you dont have a parsing program they are a good idea to check out. If you are using a weapon like a SSoY.. dont go on the raid. You need DPS fast and hard and furious. But if you're going to go the DPS route, set your minimum lvl to attend at a hard minimum of 55, otherwise, the people below that will just be feeding his lifetap, not helping at all. trust me.<br>
<br>
Well, I can't say as I have really high hopes for CoG really getting the forces together to do it (people already in alliances and rotation guilds know that attending this one would get their guild punted from the rotation so would not go near this raid) but if you guys think you can put it together then I would really love to sit near the zone, listen in and cheer you on since thats the best I can do.<br>
<br>
But as Rainne said, get on the list now, you'll have a good 4 months to debate strategy before your first shot at him as is.<br>
<br>
<br>
Lagdalen Nils'Hansen - 60 Arch Mage of Valoran<br>
Mage in the middle of a makeover!<br>
