<br>
Thanks for the great post. That is what I was hoping to &quot;spark&quot; when I started this thread. I think the bare minimum should probably be 55. I also think that there are several 55+ out there still in &quot;nameless&quot; guilds. Those are the people we are trying to get. I know our 50's stay with RKoL because either they were founding members over a year ago, or because they enjoy the environment. I am trying to save those 50's from having to leave to go to a &quot;named&quot; guild for things like VS. I've had a couple leave RKoL for a named guild because we didn't do rot mobs. RKoL isn't powerful enough and we are still a pretty new guild. (Yes a year old is still pretty new).<br>
<br>
Can CoG pull it off? I have no clue. The biggest factor of all is what you pointed out. Most can &quot;say&quot; they'll be there, but actually showing up is the problem. <p>Qamgine Nighteagle<br>
